## 3.5 Sprint E(5)- Implementation of acceptance tests, development of new forum statistics features, and enhancements to existing unit tests.

**Goal:** Implementation of automatic acceptance tests for the front-end features developed in Sprint 4.

**User Story:** As a project manager, I want the team to implement automatic acceptance tests for the front-end features developed in Sprint 4 and to develop new forum statistics features and enhancements to existing unit tests.

The especificcation:

- Implementation of automatic acceptance tests for the front-end features developed in Sprint 4, using Gherkin and WebdriverIO.
- Development of new forum statistics features.
- Creation of pages in the application that display forum statistics, accessible through a button in the header.
- Each statistic should be implemented as a React component, including the statistical value, a text field for entering a date, and a button to update the value.-
- User stories related to statistics include average comments, average messages, post with the most comments, members with the most comments, members with no activity, percentage of messages without comments, and the time of day with the most messages.
- Review of all existing unit tests to ensure they follow the AAA (Arrange-Act-Assert) model.
- Preparation of test coverage reports.

## 3.6 Sprint F(6)- Functional Requirements

**Goal:** Implementation of various functionalities and requirements, both functional and non-functional, improving aspects of testing, integration, quality and usability.

**User Story:** As a project manager, I want the team to implement the functional requirements.

The especificcation:

- Choose a user story: As a member, when viewing popular messages, messages older than five days should display the date in red text.
- Create test cases based on black box criteria.
- Check whether existing unit tests violate the single responsibility principle and correct them if necessary.
- Develop a continuous integration approach on GitHub, including compiling frontend/backend, running unit tests and performing a "smoke test" to verify minimum functionality, with results published on GitHub.
- Develop new features using BDD and TDD approaches.
- Include clarity in Git commit messages indicating the software's development phase ([Analysis], [Design], [Test], [Development], [Deployment]).
- Automated Testing and Reporting
- Automate the generation of performance/capability reports.
- Provide a test scenario with at least 25 posts, each with at least 3 comments.
- Use JMeter to run tests that include operations such as login, requesting popular, recent and unpopular posts, running statistical operations and assertions.
- Ensuring the accuracy of statistical results, as well as the correct display of background colours, dates and new text.
- Carrying out tests for different numbers of simultaneous users (10, 50, 100, 200), determining from how many users the statistical results fall below 75% and running each set of tests at least 3 times.

